 depth of sovereign and private sector debt public sector reform and the policies and political constraints on leadership on both sides of the atlantic programming open to the public includes the following talks by senior analysts visiting and in residence at the europe center at fsi josef joffe senior fellow fsi and publisher editor of die zeit robin niblett director chatham house royal institute for international affairs jacob kirkegaard peterson institute for international economics additional research and policy analysts will be added to the series throughout the year details on this series including dates of the talks are available on the european and global economic crisis series page video and podcast interviews are available at the europe center and fsi home pages related links european and global economic crisis series the europe center series search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest q&a stanford's fukuyama on european debt crisis video+ december 8 2011 cddrl fsi stanford the europe center governance project news a new view on the financial and economic crisis of 2007 2010 october 15 2010 fsi stanford the europe center news lessons from south korea's economc policy during the global financial crisis january 12 2010 shorenstein aparc ksp news national security the g20 and the global financial crisis cisac in the news democracy arsenal on april 1 2009 multiyear study of the challenges to european union integration and crisis intervention january 1 2007 fsi stanford the europe center news how can we prepare for the next global epidemic shorenstein aparc publishes new book on crisis preparedness june 7 2007 shorenstein aparc news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
